('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000001406', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000104', 6, 'sentence_simplification', 'Choose the sentence that best expresses the essential meaning of this one from paragraph 6: "Today, the method is widely used in law schools and classrooms to train students in critical thinking by challenging assumptions through dialogue and debate."', '["The Socratic Method helps students memorize key facts and rules", "The method is now used mostly in courts rather than classrooms", "Students are trained to think critically by questioning beliefs in structured discussion", "Teachers use dialogue to control debates and avoid confusion"]', '2', 'The sentence describes how the method trains critical thinking through questioning and dialogue.'),
('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000001407', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000104', 7, 'vocabulary', 'The word "skepticism" in paragraph 7 is closest in meaning to:', '["doubt", "certainty", "memory", "persuasion"]', '0', 'Skepticism means doubt or questioning attitude.'),
('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000001408', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000104', 8, 'rhetorical_purpose', 'Why does the author mention that Socrates "drank poison hemlock" in paragraph 5?', '["To show how poison was commonly used in ancient medicine", "To emphasize the tragic outcome of Socrates'' trial", "To describe how Plato reacted to Socrates'' death", "To argue that the trial was a mistake"]', '1', 'The mention of hemlock emphasizes the tragic and final outcome of Socrates'' commitment to his principles.'),
('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000001409', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000104', 9, 'insert_text', 'Where would this sentence best fit in paragraph 7: "This tension between reflection and confrontation has sparked debate among modern educators."', '["At the beginning of the paragraph", "After mentioning confrontational aspects", "After discussing skepticism", "At the end of the paragraph"]', '1', 'This sentence fits well after discussing the confrontational nature of the method.'),
('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000001410', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000104', 10, 'prose_summary', 'The Socratic Method is a form of inquiry that emphasizes questioning and dialogue to uncover deeper understanding. Choose 3 correct answers:', '["Socrates used this method to challenge accepted beliefs and stimulate reflection", "His approach differed from that of the Sophists, who prioritized persuasion", "The method gained popularity after being adopted by politicians and kings", "Despite its critics, the Socratic Method continues to be used in modern education", "Socrates created an extensive collection of philosophical writings on ethics", "His commitment to questioning ultimately led to his trial and death"]', '[0,1,3]', 'The correct answers highlight Socrates'' method of challenging beliefs, his opposition to Sophists, and the method''s continued use in education.');

