('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000001508', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000105', 8, 'rhetorical_purpose', 'Why does the author mention medical ethics in paragraph 7?', '["To demonstrate the scientific origin of utilitarianism", "To show that utilitarianism has been completely rejected", "To provide a modern example of utilitarian reasoning in practice", "To prove that utilitarianism only applies to health decisions"]', '2', 'Medical ethics is mentioned as a contemporary example of where utilitarian thinking is applied.'),
('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000001509', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000105', 9, 'insert_text', 'Where would this sentence best fit in paragraph 5: "This concern raises questions about the reliability of utilitarian judgments in everyday life."', '["At the beginning of the paragraph", "After discussing calculation difficulties", "After mentioning different conceptions of happiness", "At the end of the paragraph"]', '1', 'This sentence fits well after discussing the practical difficulty of calculating consequences.'),
('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000001510', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000105', 10, 'prose_summary', 'Utilitarianism is a moral theory that evaluates actions based on the happiness or utility they produce. Choose 3 correct answers:', '["It was developed by thinkers like Bentham and Mill, who valued consequences over intentions", "Critics argue that utilitarianism can justify actions that violate rights and moral norms", "Rule utilitarianism proposes that general principles should guide decisions to maximize happiness", "Utilitarianism is mostly used to evaluate ancient ethical codes", "Happiness, according to utilitarianism, is based solely on physical pleasure", "Despite criticism, utilitarianism continues to influence ethical discussions today"]', '[0,1,2]', 'The correct answers highlight the founders, criticisms, and rule utilitarianism as a response to criticisms.');

